{
  "texts": [
    "In practice, for macro-images that are not near a macro-critical curve (i.e.",
    "outside the extreme high magnification regime), the number of expected micro-minima (extra image pairs) is fairly low, with some simulations suggesting an approximately Poisson distribution (Granot et al. 2003).",
    "The micro-critical curves split the image plane into regions of positive and negative parity, as shown in Fig. 4.",
    "The multiplicity with which regions of positive parity overlap when mapped back to the source plane gives the mean number of positive parity images n, for which analytic formulas are given in Wambsganss (1992), Granot et al. (2003).",
    "Figure 8 shows the caustic pattern of Fig. 7, color-coded to show the number of micro-minima."
  ]
}